{"id": "duc04-testb-49:14#43", "contents": "Albright praised Primakov as a pragmatist who has cooperated with Washington on key issues in the past, but warned that the current direction of his government may jeopardize this cooperation. The United States will continue to provide aid to Russia, but will focus on promoting democracy, student exchanges, and arms control, rather than providing direct aid. Albright emphasized that foreign bailouts alone will not restore investor confidence in Russia, and that foreign investment is necessary to meet Russia's needs in the long run."}
